Dear all,

We're hiring.

http://www.jobs.ac.uk/job/ADE804/lecturer-senior-lecturer-reader/

I apologize for the drivel in the ad.  You can follow the links and get
more meaningful information about us there.  We have six jobs going, and
unofficially, we expect to hire two people in pure, two in applied, and
two in statistics.  All the jobs are permanent, at least assuming the
government doesn't do away with universities entirely.

On behalf of the School of Mathematics and Statistics, I am happy to
confirm the truth of the advertisement's statement that "Preference may be
given to candidates in Pure Mathematics, Applied Mathematics, and
Statistics."

Tom







